  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink286-kilavi">uṭaṉpōkkut tuṇinta talaimakaṉ aḵt oḻintu tāṉē varaiviṭai vaittup piriya niṉaintataṉaik kuṟippiṉāṉ uṇarnta talaimakaḷ toḻikkuc colliyatu; 
          talaimakaṉ varaiviṭai vaittup pirival eṉṟa vaḻit talaimakaḷ tōḻikkuc colliyatūum ām.
           </p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> What the heroine said to the confidante, having understood from his indication that the hero—who had [originally] been resolved on elopement—had abandoned that and instead intended to fix the marriage and then separate; it may also be taken as what the heroine said to the confidante on the occasion when the hero, having fixed the marriage, said “I will separate”.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink286">
<l>ciṟutiṉai koyta viruvi veṇkāṟ</l>
<l>kāytta vavaraip paṭukiḷi kaṭiyum</l>
<l>yāṇa rākiya naṉmalai nāṭaṉ</l>
<l>pukariṉṟu nayantaṉaṉ pōluṅ</l>
<l>kavarun tōḻiyeṉ māmaik kaviṉē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>The man from the good mountain that became fertile—</l>
        <l rend="indent">where parakeets descend on ripened field-beans</l>
        <l rend="indent">among the white stalks of stubble </l>
        <l rend="indent">harvested [for their] small millet—</l>

        <l>seems to yearn [for me] without fault.</l>
        <l>But [what] he [truly] does is seize my dark beauty, O friend!</l>

      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
